#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/switzerland.rst:150
msgid ""
"Switzerland uses a specific, localized version of the :ref:`ISO 20022 XML "
"global standard <accounting/sepa_payments/pain>`. To select the appropriate "
"Swiss version for your company, open the **Accounting** app, and navigate "
"to :menuselection:`Configuration --> Journals`. Then, open the relevant "
"**Bank** journal, and in the :guilabel:`Outgoing Payments`, "
"select :guilabel:`Swiss` from the :guilabel:`SEPA Pain Version` field."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/switzerland.rst:157
msgid "The **SEPA Module** in Odoo covers both SEPA *and* ISO 20022 payments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../content/applications/finance/fiscal_localizations/switzerland.rst:166
msgid ""
"By default, the XML files for outgoing payments generated by Odoo use the "
"Swiss-specific **PAIN.001.001.03.ch.02** format. If your bank requires the "
"newer **PAIN.001.001.09** version, open the **Accounting** and go "
"to :menuselection:`Configuration --> Journals`. Open the relevant **Bank**, "
"and in the :guilabel:`Outgoing Payments` tab, set the :guilabel:`SEPA Pain "
"version` field to :guilabel:`New generic version (09)`."
msgstr ""

